quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  77,41,"As for the righteous, they will be amid shade and springs"
  77,42,"And fruits, all they desire"
  77,43,"“Eat and drink to your heart’s content, for all that you did"
  77,44,We certainly reward the doers of good
  77,45,Ah woe that day to the rejecters of truth
  77,46,"Eat and enjoy yourselves a little while, because you are wrong-doers"
  77,47,Ah woe that day to the rejecters of truth
  77,48,"And when it is said to them, “Prostrate yourselves,” they do not do so"
  77,49,Ah woe that day to the rejecters of truth
  77,50,Then in what message after that will they believe? 50 (End of Part)